Wigan goalkeeper Ali Al-Habsi has seen Australia goalkeeper Mat Ryan up close - and is in no doubt that he is the man to solve Liverpool's goalkeeping problems.

Al-Habsi was Ryan's opposite number as Australia beat Oman 4-0 in the Asian Cup last Tuesday but the result could have turned differently after an astonishing save from Ryan kept out a volley from Raed Salah two minutes into the game.

'He's brilliant,' Al-Habsi raved to FourFourTwo. 'He has been fantastic in the World Cup and here in the Asian Cup.'

