Liverpool's first-choice stopper Simon Mignolet has appeared bereft of confidence throughout the season and his untidy footwork has hindered the passing movements that Brendan Rodgers likes to see his team build from defence.

Brad Jones replaced Mignolet in the side for what was intended to be an indefinite period before sustaining a thigh injury against Burnley during the Christmas fixtures. 

And with Rodgers enforcing a recruitment policy of young players with great potential, Al-Habsi believes 22-year-old Ryan would be a perfect signing at Anfield.

'He's young, he can only improve and, of course Liverpool is a big club and for him it would be a great chance to make it.' 

